WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.134 --> 00:00:04.071
Previously on
"Gotham Knights"...

2
00:00:04.104 --> 00:00:05.540
We've been set up.

3
00:00:05.573 --> 00:00:06.750
Thousands have lined the streets

4
00:00:06.774 --> 00:00:07.809
to honor the city's

5
00:00:07.842 --> 00:00:09.309
fallen hero Bruce Wayne.

6
00:00:09.343 --> 00:00:12.112
who Gotham has now
learned was Batman.

7
00:00:12.145 --> 00:00:15.617
Wayne is survived by
his son Turner Hayes.

8
00:00:17.084 --> 00:00:20.187
Your father had
Alfred. You have me.

9
00:00:20.220 --> 00:00:21.532
This makes it look
like the person

10
00:00:21.556 --> 00:00:23.390
who paid to have your
dad killed is you.

11
00:00:23.423 --> 00:00:25.092
They think I killed my dad

12
00:00:25.125 --> 00:00:26.761
because I wanted his money?

13
00:00:26.794 --> 00:00:28.328
It's the bat brat.

14
00:00:28.362 --> 00:00:30.798
The night he was killed. this
was found on your father.

15
00:00:30.832 --> 00:00:33.601
All aboard the
Blackgate Express.

16
00:00:33.635 --> 00:00:35.168
Uhh!

17
00:00:38.372 --> 00:00:39.807
Your little attempt at escape

18
00:00:39.841 --> 00:00:41.743
just made my job
a little easier.

19
00:00:41.776 --> 00:00:43.578
He's in on it. They all are.

20
00:00:46.748 --> 00:00:47.849
Who the hell are you?

21
00:00:47.882 --> 00:00:49.082
I'm Robin.

22
00:00:49.116 --> 00:00:50.217
We are marshaling

23
00:00:50.250 --> 00:00:52.152
all of the city's resources

24
00:00:52.185 --> 00:00:54.689
to hunt down these fugitives.

25
00:00:54.722 --> 00:00:58.191
Harper and Cullen Row.
the Joker's daughter.

26
00:00:58.225 --> 00:01:00.294
and Bruce Wayne's own son.

27
00:01:00.327 --> 00:01:02.030
We're gonna find who
really killed my dad

28
00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:03.565
and clear our names.

29
00:01:03.598 --> 00:01:05.265
It's the symbol of
the Court of Owls.

30
00:01:05.299 --> 00:01:06.911
They're the ones who
really run this city.

31
00:01:06.935 --> 00:01:08.703
No one knows who they are

32
00:01:08.736 --> 00:01:10.939
'cause if you find out...

33
00:01:10.972 --> 00:01:13.608
it'll be the last
thing you ever see.

34
00:01:31.191 --> 00:01:32.492
Negative. negative.

35
00:01:33.695 --> 00:01:34.729
Clear.

36
00:01:47.207 --> 00:01:49.077
Did you know about this?

37
00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:51.311
Bruce shared many
secrets with me

38
00:01:51.345 --> 00:01:52.880
but this wasn't one of them.

39
00:01:54.782 --> 00:01:56.316
Bag and tag everything.

40
00:01:56.350 --> 00:01:57.952
Let's go. Pack up
all the security.

41
00:01:57.986 --> 00:01:59.419
But the irony...
People who couldn't

42
00:01:59.453 --> 00:02:01.221
stop crime in Gotham
treating the man

43
00:02:01.254 --> 00:02:03.691
who did like a criminal.

44
00:02:03.725 --> 00:02:05.125
Bruce was my friend.

45
00:02:06.094 --> 00:02:07.996
So was Turner.

46
00:02:08.029 --> 00:02:09.764
Will you bag and
tag him as well?

47
00:02:40.928 --> 00:02:44.799
Hey. This is totally you.

48
00:02:44.832 --> 00:02:46.901
Matches your new hair.

49
00:02:46.934 --> 00:02:49.169
And you clearly
don't know me at all.

50
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.439
OK. Now.

51
00:02:52.472 --> 00:02:55.510
We got most wanted.
Wanted most.

52
00:02:55.543 --> 00:02:57.111
Take 'em both. Decide later.

53
00:02:58.445 --> 00:03:00.782
Guys. Only grab what we need.

54
00:03:00.815 --> 00:03:02.650
I absolutely need this.

55
00:03:02.684 --> 00:03:05.485
well. $1.200 jacket
and the matching kicks.

56
00:03:07.220 --> 00:03:09.256
We discussed this.
It's more of a loan.

57
00:03:09.289 --> 00:03:11.626
Once we clear our names.
we're paying it back.

58
00:03:11.659 --> 00:03:13.795
Right. Just as soon
as the store pays back

59
00:03:13.828 --> 00:03:16.229
all the child labor they
exploited to make this stuff.

60
00:03:16.263 --> 00:03:18.800
Well. you know if you
victimize the victimizer.

61
00:03:18.833 --> 00:03:20.267
then it's a victimless crime.

62
00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:22.436
I'm not sure the law
sees it that way.

63
00:03:22.469 --> 00:03:24.906
Just as long as they
don't see you. right?

64
00:03:27.441 --> 00:03:29.010
Not exactly my style.

65
00:03:29.043 --> 00:03:30.277
Mm-hmm. That's the point.

66
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:31.421
We gotta change up
our looks so that

67
00:03:31.445 --> 00:03:33.346
we don't match our mugshots.

68
00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:35.083
I really wish they'd
taken that turtleneck

69
00:03:35.116 --> 00:03:36.684
when they seized
your trust fund.

70
00:03:37.885 --> 00:03:41.221
Hey. You're a
fugitive now. OK?

71
00:03:41.254 --> 00:03:43.457
You are no longer required
to be this boring.

72
00:03:43.490 --> 00:03:45.258
Come on. What happened
to that guy who

73
00:03:45.292 --> 00:03:47.494
grabbed the wheel and
wrecked the prison transport?

74
00:03:47.528 --> 00:03:49.564
That guy that I know
you keep tucked away.

75
00:03:49.597 --> 00:03:51.866
hiding underneath
all that cashmere?

76
00:03:53.266 --> 00:03:55.203
Let me know when he wants
to come out and play.

77
00:03:58.305 --> 00:04:00.240
OK. who tripped
the silent alarm?

78
00:04:03.077 --> 00:04:04.411
Attention. shoplifters.

79
00:04:04.444 --> 00:04:06.147
please make your
final selections

80
00:04:06.180 --> 00:04:08.883
and kindly bring them
towards the rear exit.

81
00:04:23.765 --> 00:04:26.567
Carrie? What are
you doing here?

82
00:04:26.601 --> 00:04:28.603
Responding to a
burglary in progress.

83
00:04:35.308 --> 00:04:36.711
You know anything about that?

84
00:04:57.732 --> 00:05:00.201
As the manhunt continues
for Turner Hayes

85
00:05:00.234 --> 00:05:01.869
and the band of
criminals wanted for

86
00:05:01.903 --> 00:05:03.303
the murder of Bruce Wayne.

87
00:05:03.336 --> 00:05:04.872
Mayor Hill announced
that he's created

88
00:05:04.906 --> 00:05:06.473
a blue ribbon task force

89
00:05:06.507 --> 00:05:09.177
spearheaded by District
Attorney Harvey Dent

90
00:05:09.210 --> 00:05:10.845
to apprehend the fugitives.

91
00:05:10.878 --> 00:05:13.548
No matter where the hunt
leads. we'll drag those killers

92
00:05:13.581 --> 00:05:17.552
out of whatever sleaze-infested
back alley they're holed up in.

93
00:05:21.055 --> 00:05:22.890
Um. I do not see
what the big deal is.

94
00:05:22.924 --> 00:05:24.826
I just needed to pick
up some accessories.

95
00:05:24.859 --> 00:05:27.595
You're all supposed to
be keeping a low profile.

96
00:05:27.628 --> 00:05:31.165
Oh. and dyeing your hair blue
isn't exactly blending in.

97
00:05:31.199 --> 00:05:32.300
This is Gotham.

98
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:33.534
You blend in by standing out.

99
00:05:33.568 --> 00:05:35.303
We needed supplies.

100
00:05:35.335 --> 00:05:36.814
Sure. we have our run
of this place at night.

101
00:05:36.838 --> 00:05:39.307
Food from the kitchen.
Showers in the gym.

102
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:41.108
But clothes are another story.

103
00:05:41.142 --> 00:05:43.044
Trust me... the lost and found

104
00:05:43.077 --> 00:05:44.912
is... slim pickings.

105
00:05:46.280 --> 00:05:48.049
But committing crime
isn't the best way

106
00:05:48.082 --> 00:05:49.449
to prove you're innocent.

107
00:05:49.482 --> 00:05:51.953
And how are we
supposed to do that?

108
00:05:51.986 --> 00:05:53.621
Our leads don't lead anywhere.

109
00:05:53.654 --> 00:05:54.922
and that detective who tried to

110
00:05:54.956 --> 00:05:57.091
frame/kill us is dirty.

111
00:05:57.124 --> 00:05:59.293
So. have fun calling
the cops on a cop.

112
00:05:59.327 --> 00:06:00.436
And I'm not sure how
many clues we can get

113
00:06:00.460 --> 00:06:01.796
from a watch engraved with

114
00:06:01.829 --> 00:06:03.698
the symbol of some
evil bird cult.

115
00:06:03.731 --> 00:06:06.433
Laugh while you can.

116
00:06:06.466 --> 00:06:08.368
Court of Owls controls
this entire city.

117
00:06:08.401 --> 00:06:09.770
They have eyes everywhere.

118
00:06:09.804 --> 00:06:11.639
And yet no one has
ever seen them.

119
00:06:11.672 --> 00:06:13.440
No one who lived
to tell about it.

120
00:06:13.473 --> 00:06:15.142
Right. right. right. right.

121
00:06:15.176 --> 00:06:17.211
"Speak not a
whispered word of them

122
00:06:17.245 --> 00:06:19.479
or they'll send the
Talon for your head."

123
00:06:20.648 --> 00:06:22.415
Let's just tell the cops.

124
00:06:22.449 --> 00:06:24.852
No. really. A
nursery rhyme did it.

125
00:06:26.087 --> 00:06:27.688
She's right.

126
00:06:27.722 --> 00:06:29.790
We need something a little
more tangible to go on.

127
00:06:30.725 --> 00:06:32.425
I have a friend working on that.

128
00:06:43.838 --> 00:06:45.506
First two periods are cancelled.

129
00:06:45.539 --> 00:06:46.583
and they're having
an assembly to

130
00:06:46.607 --> 00:06:48.408
talk to us about Turner.

131
00:06:48.441 --> 00:06:50.220
You'd think your classmate
becoming the most wanted

132
00:06:50.244 --> 00:06:52.380
fugitive in Gotham
since Ed Nygma

133
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:53.381
would give us the whole day off.

134
00:06:53.413 --> 00:06:54.682
He didn't do it. OK?

135
00:06:54.715 --> 00:06:55.750
Come on.

136
00:06:55.783 --> 00:06:57.023
Money from his bank account was

137
00:06:57.051 --> 00:06:58.019
paid to the killers.

138
00:06:58.052 --> 00:06:59.020
And if he were guilty.

139
00:06:59.053 --> 00:07:00.187
then why would he ask me

140
00:07:00.221 --> 00:07:01.231
to hack the banks to find out

141
00:07:01.255 --> 00:07:02.957
how that money got there?

142
00:07:02.990 --> 00:07:04.859
You... you did what?

143
00:07:06.294 --> 00:07:07.460
Used his dad's Batcomputer

144
00:07:07.494 --> 00:07:09.363
to try to prove he was innocent.

145
00:07:09.397 --> 00:07:10.774
I'm sorry. I'm just
trying to figure out

146
00:07:10.798 --> 00:07:13.034
which part of that
sounds more insane...

147
00:07:13.067 --> 00:07:15.403
The fact that you hacked the
city's financial infrastructure

148
00:07:15.435 --> 00:07:17.705
or that you did it
on a Batcomputer.

149
00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:20.684
Do you understand how much
trouble you could've gotten in?

150
00:07:20.708 --> 00:07:22.510
I'm more worried about
the trouble he's in.

151
00:07:22.543 --> 00:07:23.878
because I'm his friend.

152
00:07:23.911 --> 00:07:25.413
Well. you could
become an accessory

153
00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:26.747
if you keep helping him.

154
00:07:26.781 --> 00:07:29.617
Steph. He's going
to get caught.

155
00:07:29.650 --> 00:07:32.019
and when he does. he's gonna
bring you down with him.

156
00:07:32.053 --> 00:07:33.263
I mean. the guy
couldn't even figure out

157
00:07:33.287 --> 00:07:34.855
his dad was Batman.

158
00:07:34.889 --> 00:07:37.358
Where the hell is he gonna hide?

159
00:08:33.581 --> 00:08:35.850
Hmm. Looks like someone

160
00:08:35.883 --> 00:08:38.986
took a wrong turn at
cheerleader tryouts.

161
00:08:39.020 --> 00:08:40.721
We don't have cheerleaders
at this school.

162
00:08:40.755 --> 00:08:42.656
Hmm. Their loss.
'cause you are

163
00:08:42.690 --> 00:08:45.026
rockin' that skirt. blondie.

164
00:08:46.027 --> 00:08:48.529
- Thank you.
- Duela!

165
00:08:48.562 --> 00:08:50.765
Duela. let her go.

166
00:08:50.798 --> 00:08:52.433
She's my friend.
You can trust her.

167
00:08:52.466 --> 00:08:53.634
I don't trust you.

168
00:08:53.667 --> 00:08:55.102
Who the hell is she?

169
00:08:55.136 --> 00:08:56.971
Stephanie. Hi.

170
00:08:57.004 --> 00:08:59.140
I thought you said no one
else knew about this place.

171
00:08:59.173 --> 00:09:01.609
She's the only other person.
Duela. put the knife down.

172
00:09:01.642 --> 00:09:02.877
- Or what?
- Or you might

173
00:09:02.910 --> 00:09:04.211
kill the one person who can

174
00:09:04.245 --> 00:09:05.846
prove we were set up.

175
00:09:05.880 --> 00:09:07.124
She's looking into
where the money

176
00:09:07.148 --> 00:09:08.349
you were paid came from.

177
00:09:08.382 --> 00:09:09.650
This is the hacker chick?

178
00:09:09.683 --> 00:09:11.986
Hacker chick. Hi.

179
00:09:12.019 --> 00:09:15.222
Stephanie... Brown?

180
00:09:15.256 --> 00:09:17.024
As in Arthur Brown?

181
00:09:18.559 --> 00:09:21.228
Are you the daughter of
the "Quiz Bowl" host?

182
00:09:21.262 --> 00:09:22.863
I think I prefer
"Hacker chick."

183
00:09:24.098 --> 00:09:26.667
'Cause that is what
this group was missing.

184
00:09:26.700 --> 00:09:28.636
A celebrity game
show host's kid.

185
00:09:28.669 --> 00:09:30.237
So. you're the one
who's gonna take

186
00:09:30.271 --> 00:09:31.605
all those ones and zeros

187
00:09:31.639 --> 00:09:33.140
and make 'em prove
we're innocent?

188
00:09:33.174 --> 00:09:34.575
That was the plan.

189
00:09:34.608 --> 00:09:35.876
until the GCPD impounded

190
00:09:35.910 --> 00:09:37.611
everything in the Batcave.

191
00:09:39.146 --> 00:09:40.347
So. the Batcomputer?

192
00:09:51.592 --> 00:09:54.395
Harvey. have you
seen Detective Ford?

193
00:09:54.428 --> 00:09:55.896
Uh. not in a while.

194
00:09:55.930 --> 00:09:57.898
He's been dodging my calls.

195
00:09:57.932 --> 00:09:59.934
Well. he better not dodge mine.

196
00:10:07.374 --> 00:10:09.210
Is that his phone?

197
00:10:46.814 --> 00:10:48.315
We better check on his team.

198
00:10:49.584 --> 00:10:51.218
Uh... uh.

199
00:11:09.003 --> 00:11:11.606
6 members of the GCPD task force

200
00:11:11.640 --> 00:11:13.474
assigned to hunt
down the fugitives

201
00:11:13.508 --> 00:11:15.676
wanted for the
murder of Bruce Wayne

202
00:11:15.709 --> 00:11:18.245
have themselves
been found murdered.

203
00:11:18.279 --> 00:11:21.348
The gruesome discovery was
made earlier this morning.

204
00:11:21.382 --> 00:11:23.317
The GCPD declined to comment

205
00:11:23.350 --> 00:11:25.620
on an ongoing investigation.

206
00:11:25.654 --> 00:11:27.688
but sources within the
department say that

207
00:11:27.721 --> 00:11:31.192
each of those detectives
was decapitated.

208
00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:36.096
"Or they'll send the
Talon for your head."

209
00:11:38.799 --> 00:11:40.868
Oh! Oh. I'm sorry.
What was that?

210
00:11:40.901 --> 00:11:42.571
Maybe... maybe Duela
was right about

211
00:11:42.604 --> 00:11:44.047
how dangerous and...
Say it with me now...

212
00:11:44.071 --> 00:11:45.906
How real the Court of Owls is.

213
00:11:45.940 --> 00:11:47.676
Why would they kill
Ford and his men?

214
00:11:47.708 --> 00:11:49.343
Because they screwed
up killing us.

215
00:11:49.376 --> 00:11:52.213
OK. OK. Say they are real.

216
00:11:52.246 --> 00:11:53.714
Who is gonna believe us?

217
00:11:53.747 --> 00:11:55.115
My dad would've.

218
00:11:55.149 --> 00:11:56.951
If the world's greatest
detective was found

219
00:11:56.984 --> 00:11:58.886
holding a Court of Owls coin.

220
00:11:58.919 --> 00:12:00.754
I'll bet he knew
something about them.

221
00:12:00.788 --> 00:12:02.691
Maybe he got too close to them

222
00:12:02.723 --> 00:12:04.158
and that's what got him killed.

223
00:12:04.191 --> 00:12:05.869
Oh. and now you want us
to end up just like him?

224
00:12:05.893 --> 00:12:08.862
No. I want to pick
up where he left off.

225
00:12:08.896 --> 00:12:10.599
And how do we do that?

226
00:12:10.632 --> 00:12:11.932
There is one way.

227
00:12:13.602 --> 00:12:15.336
But it's a terrible idea.

228
00:12:15.369 --> 00:12:16.737
Never stopped us before.

229
00:12:16.770 --> 00:12:18.172
They got Bruce's journals.

230
00:12:18.205 --> 00:12:19.773
He kept records of
all of his cases.

231
00:12:19.807 --> 00:12:21.610
I never saw any
journals in the house.

232
00:12:21.643 --> 00:12:23.019
That's because
they're not in there.

233
00:12:23.043 --> 00:12:25.312
Um. they're in his
office in Wayne Tower

234
00:12:25.346 --> 00:12:26.681
in a secret compartment.

235
00:12:26.715 --> 00:12:28.148
We'd have to break
in to get them.

236
00:12:34.154 --> 00:12:36.323
You're right. That
is a terrible idea.

237
00:12:36.357 --> 00:12:37.635
But we need to find
out everything we can

238
00:12:37.659 --> 00:12:38.926
about who's after us.

239
00:12:38.959 --> 00:12:40.695
and who would know better than

240
00:12:40.729 --> 00:12:43.632
the last person they
targeted? My dad.

241
00:12:43.665 --> 00:12:44.675
You know. this isn't
like breaking into

242
00:12:44.699 --> 00:12:46.433
Daddy's liquor cabinet.

243
00:12:46.467 --> 00:12:48.737
I know. It's more
like something the guy

244
00:12:48.769 --> 00:12:49.813
who grabbed the
wheel and wrecked

245
00:12:49.837 --> 00:12:51.640
the transport would do.

246
00:12:51.673 --> 00:12:53.107
So. you swipe one leather jacket

247
00:12:53.140 --> 00:12:55.109
and suddenly you're
a master thief?

248
00:12:55.142 --> 00:12:57.211
No. But it's a
good thing I know

249
00:12:57.244 --> 00:12:59.013
some people who are.

250
00:13:17.931 --> 00:13:19.900
You do realize the first
rule they teach you

251
00:13:19.933 --> 00:13:21.468
in thief school
is never return to

252
00:13:21.503 --> 00:13:23.672
the scene of a crime. right?

253
00:13:23.705 --> 00:13:25.507
Since when do you
follow the rules?

254
00:13:25.540 --> 00:13:27.542
Uh. since Daddy's
power tower became

255
00:13:27.575 --> 00:13:30.277
the most famous crime scene
in the history of Gotham.

256
00:13:30.311 --> 00:13:32.346
Not to mention they'll
have doubled the security.

257
00:13:32.379 --> 00:13:34.081
restored the motion
sensors we disabled.

258
00:13:34.114 --> 00:13:35.916
and have redundant
cameras covering

259
00:13:35.949 --> 00:13:37.686
every way in or out.

260
00:13:37.719 --> 00:13:38.986
All but one.

261
00:13:40.789 --> 00:13:43.023
My dad had a private elevator.

262
00:13:43.057 --> 00:13:44.735
Goes all the way from the
lowest level of the garage

263
00:13:44.759 --> 00:13:45.893
