275
00:14:07.281 --> 00:14:09.883
OK. all due respect to
Daddy's Batproverbs.

276
00:14:09.917 --> 00:14:11.251
but what the hell
does that mean?

277
00:14:11.285 --> 00:14:12.886
It means the most
vulnerable areas

278
00:14:12.920 --> 00:14:14.264
are the ones you're
not worried about.

279
00:14:14.288 --> 00:14:15.923
Wayne Security vehicles
are equipped with

280
00:14:15.956 --> 00:14:17.768
transponders that
automatically open the gates.

281
00:14:17.792 --> 00:14:19.893
Their way of keeping
people out is our way in.

282
00:14:19.927 --> 00:14:21.971
Oh. OK. so. your solution
to breaking into a building

283
00:14:21.995 --> 00:14:23.464
is breaking into a car.

284
00:14:24.965 --> 00:14:27.267
Nobody has to risk any more
than they already have.

285
00:14:27.301 --> 00:14:28.503
I can go in alone.

286
00:14:28.536 --> 00:14:30.672
Not gonna happen. I'm in.

287
00:14:30.705 --> 00:14:31.972
Ugh.

288
00:14:33.140 --> 00:14:34.752
You're gonna need someone
to keep the engine running.

289
00:14:34.776 --> 00:14:36.443
And if you want to even

290
00:14:36.477 --> 00:14:39.346
get the engine running.
you're gonna need me.

291
00:14:41.750 --> 00:14:43.183
I was hoping you'd say that.

292
00:14:43.217 --> 00:14:44.662
because I just happen to
know where a couple of

293
00:14:44.686 --> 00:14:45.653
Wayne Security vehicles

294
00:14:45.687 --> 00:14:47.121
might be lying around.

295
00:14:50.023 --> 00:14:52.192
Whatever gets me
out of this attic.

296
00:14:54.829 --> 00:14:57.998
Do you like numbers? I do.

297
00:14:58.031 --> 00:15:01.068
They're the only things in
this city that don't lie.

298
00:15:01.101 --> 00:15:03.470
So. let's talk numbers.

299
00:15:03.505 --> 00:15:06.073
7. That's how many toe tags

300
00:15:06.106 --> 00:15:07.876
