508
00:26:54.248 --> 00:26:57.384
Let's go!

509
00:26:57.418 --> 00:26:58.719
Come on. come on!

510
00:27:03.691 --> 00:27:05.826
Uhh!

511
00:27:05.860 --> 00:27:06.894
Aah!

512
00:27:08.295 --> 00:27:09.730
Uhh!

513
00:27:09.763 --> 00:27:11.632
Could use some help here. guys.

514
00:27:20.474 --> 00:27:22.143
Come on. guys. we have to go.

515
00:27:22.176 --> 00:27:24.221
Can't get out that way.
Garage is crawling with GCPD.

516
00:27:24.245 --> 00:27:25.889
Well. we're definitely
not getting out that way.

517
00:27:25.913 --> 00:27:29.683
- Then we're trapped.
- Uhh! Uhh!

518
00:27:29.717 --> 00:27:31.018
There is one way.

519
00:27:34.088 --> 00:27:35.122
How? Climb?

520
00:27:35.156 --> 00:27:37.358
No. We fly.

521
00:27:41.228 --> 00:27:43.430
Have you ever used
that thing before?

522
00:27:43.464 --> 00:27:45.332
Don't answer that.

523
00:27:45.366 --> 00:27:47.701
It's a 48-story drop. so.

524
00:27:47.735 --> 00:27:50.204
you know... don't let go.

525
00:28:28.643 --> 00:28:29.877
Ahem.

526
00:28:34.583 --> 00:28:36.585
As advertised.

527
00:28:36.618 --> 00:28:38.719
Genuine Sicolo.
Limited edition.

528
00:28:38.752 --> 00:28:40.821
Skeleton dial.
Polished camphors.

529
00:28:40.854 --> 00:28:42.756
Tells time. too.

530
00:28:42.790 --> 00:28:45.192
You neglected to
mention an engraving.

531
00:28:45.226 --> 00:28:48.329
OK. so. knock a few bucks
off the sticker price.

532
00:28:48.362 --> 00:28:50.898
It's quite a unique feature.

533
00:28:50.931 --> 00:28:54.134
Is this what makes
it so sought-after?

534
00:28:55.604 --> 00:28:57.338
What do you mean. sought-after?

535
00:28:57.371 --> 00:29:00.575
When I called around
to ascertain the value.

536
00:29:00.609 --> 00:29:02.076
there was one potential buyer

537
00:29:02.109 --> 00:29:05.980
who was quite interested
in this particular model.

538
00:29:06.013 --> 00:29:08.015
Willing to pay a fortune.

539
00:29:08.048 --> 00:29:11.720
And willing to pay even more

540
00:29:11.752 --> 00:29:14.121
for the person selling it.

541
00:29:21.295 --> 00:29:22.731
I don't get it.
Why would Duela

542
00:29:22.763 --> 00:29:23.864
screw us over like that?

543
00:29:23.897 --> 00:29:24.975
She's the Joker's daughter.

544
00:29:24.999 --> 00:29:26.500
I'm surprised it
took her this long.

545
00:29:26.534 --> 00:29:28.035
How much could she have possibly

546
00:29:28.068 --> 00:29:29.370
been offered for that watch?

547
00:29:29.403 --> 00:29:31.047
I'm not sure you want to
put a price tag on betrayal

548
00:29:31.071 --> 00:29:32.683
but I'm pretty sure a
personalized engraving

549
00:29:32.707 --> 00:29:34.709
makes it worth less. not more.

550
00:29:34.743 --> 00:29:37.378
That depends on the buyer

551
00:29:37.411 --> 00:29:38.513
and the engraving.

552
00:29:43.050 --> 00:29:45.986
Oh. please tell me you
are not this stupid.

553
00:29:46.020 --> 00:29:49.356
Unwise to insult the
person holding the gun.

554
00:29:49.390 --> 00:29:50.525
Considering what's coming.

555
00:29:50.558 --> 00:29:52.326
I would rather be shot.

556
00:29:52.359 --> 00:29:54.729
You have no idea who
you're dealing with.

557
00:29:54.763 --> 00:29:56.897
Nor do I care.

558
00:29:56.930 --> 00:29:59.867
At this price point.
I don't ask questions.

559
00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:03.170
Look... whatever
they're paying you

560
00:30:03.203 --> 00:30:05.439
will be going towards
your funeral costs. OK.

561
00:30:05.472 --> 00:30:07.350
because the Court of Owls
is not really in the...

562
00:30:07.374 --> 00:30:09.109
The leaving loose
ends kind of business.

563
00:30:09.143 --> 00:30:10.743
and that's what both
of us are dealing...

564
00:30:52.687 --> 00:30:54.955
Aah!

565
00:31:28.723 --> 00:31:30.525
No-no-no-no-no-no-no.

566
00:31:39.834 --> 00:31:40.802
Uhh!

567
00:31:40.835 --> 00:31:42.469
No!

568
00:31:46.875 --> 00:31:48.510
Aah! Uhh!

569
00:32:00.120 --> 00:32:01.623
Uhh.

570
00:32:05.259 --> 00:32:06.493
Uhh.

571
00:32:06.528 --> 00:32:08.328
Huh?

572
00:32:12.966 --> 00:32:14.669
Uhh.

573
00:32:46.935 --> 00:32:49.704
Hey! Come on! Get
me out of here!

574
00:33:11.225 --> 00:33:12.527
Aah!

575
00:33:12.560 --> 00:33:13.628
Hit the deck!

576
00:33:34.147 --> 00:33:35.917
How many more of those you got?

577
00:33:35.950 --> 00:33:37.384
Not enough.

578
00:33:40.588 --> 00:33:42.089
- Run!
- Yeah.

579
00:33:46.326 --> 00:33:47.361
Uhh.

580
00:34:07.649 --> 00:34:08.917
Thanks.

581
00:34:08.950 --> 00:34:10.417
Just change it every 12 hours.

582
00:34:10.450 --> 00:34:12.687
No. I mean for
coming back for me.

583
00:34:12.720 --> 00:34:13.755
Don't thank us.

584
00:34:14.956 --> 00:34:16.591
If we'd gone with
you. we'd be dead.

585
00:34:16.624 --> 00:34:18.624
And if it were up to us.
we would've left your ass.

586
00:34:19.493 --> 00:34:22.429
You want to thank
someone? Thank him.

587
00:34:33.541 --> 00:34:36.243
That was pretty
stupid. you know.

588
00:34:36.276 --> 00:34:37.655
thinking that you
could go up against

589
00:34:37.679 --> 00:34:38.780
the Talon like that.

590
00:34:39.981 --> 00:34:41.481
I had help.

591
00:34:41.516 --> 00:34:43.785
I guess that's why
I'm still alive.

592
00:34:53.995 --> 00:34:57.364
Look. I know we all
wanna kill each other.

593
00:34:58.566 --> 00:35:00.434
But if we stick together.
we have a better shot

594
00:35:00.467 --> 00:35:01.736
at keeping the Court of Owls

595
00:35:01.769 --> 00:35:03.170
from doing it for us.

596
00:35:04.137 --> 00:35:05.305
Well. you almost got kabobed

597
00:35:05.339 --> 00:35:06.841
getting Daddy's diary.

598
00:35:08.108 --> 00:35:09.343
Was it worth it?

599
00:35:10.912 --> 00:35:12.112
Yeah.

600
00:35:13.146 --> 00:35:15.182
You ever stop to think
maybe you are. too?

601
00:35:20.088 --> 00:35:24.224
Hey. Um... you're...
pretty good

602
00:35:24.257 --> 00:35:26.193
with that sword. you know.

603
00:35:26.226 --> 00:35:27.795
It's nice to know
Bruce Wayne's kid

604
00:35:27.829 --> 00:35:29.731
can wield more than
a dessert fork.

605
00:35:31.431 --> 00:35:33.467
You know. back in
my old neighborhood.

606
00:35:33.500 --> 00:35:36.037
all I wanted was to
play street hockey.

607
00:35:36.070 --> 00:35:37.705
But when I was adopted.
my dad insisted

608
00:35:37.739 --> 00:35:41.009
that I learn martial
arts and fencing.

609
00:35:41.042 --> 00:35:42.342
to get good at
them. be the best.

610
00:35:42.376 --> 00:35:44.311
Lucky for you he did.

611
00:35:44.344 --> 00:35:46.213
I don't think it was luck.

612
00:35:46.246 --> 00:35:47.582
or coincidence.

613
00:35:49.117 --> 00:35:50.226
Makes me wonder what
else he might've

614
00:35:50.250 --> 00:35:52.285
been preparing me for.

615
00:36:03.131 --> 00:36:04.398
What the hell are you doing?

616
00:36:04.431 --> 00:36:05.733
You think ratting
me out is gonna

617
00:36:05.767 --> 00:36:06.777
stop me from helping Turner?

618
00:36:06.801 --> 00:36:07.935
I didn't rat you out.

619
00:36:07.969 --> 00:36:09.137
Oh. really? Oh. what were you

620
00:36:09.169 --> 00:36:10.470
in there doing for over an hour?

621
00:36:13.173 --> 00:36:14.709
I told them that I did it.

622
00:36:14.742 --> 00:36:17.545
that I was the one who
hacked those banks.

623
00:36:17.578 --> 00:36:18.846
- What?
- I said that Turner

624
00:36:18.880 --> 00:36:20.280
asked you to do it. but

625
00:36:20.313 --> 00:36:21.281
you didn't wanna
break the law for him.

626
00:36:21.314 --> 00:36:23.350
so. I did it.

627
00:36:23.383 --> 00:36:24.886
To help my friend.

628
00:36:26.319 --> 00:36:27.689
Why would you do that?

629
00:36:30.591 --> 00:36:31.969
I just couldn't sit
here and watch you

630
00:36:31.993 --> 00:36:33.326
screw up your life.

631
00:36:33.360 --> 00:36:34.595
Not for that guy.

632
00:36:34.629 --> 00:36:36.931
What about you?
Weren't you the one

633
00:36:36.964 --> 00:36:38.432
lecturing me on
getting in trouble?

634
00:36:38.465 --> 00:36:40.568
Just as long as I can
keep you out of it.

635
00:36:41.769 --> 00:36:42.804
I can't let you do that.

636
00:36:42.837 --> 00:36:44.639
You didn't ask me to.

637
00:36:44.672 --> 00:36:47.240
I guess that's the difference
between me and Turner.

638
00:36:59.419 --> 00:37:01.421
System says that they
accessed the building

639
00:37:01.455 --> 00:37:03.791
using Bruce Wayne's
personal code.

640
00:37:03.825 --> 00:37:05.560
What was taken?

641
00:37:05.593 --> 00:37:08.930
According to the
inventory. just the sword.

642
00:37:11.165 --> 00:37:13.333
Why risk coming
back for a sword?

643
00:37:13.366 --> 00:37:15.302
I don't know.

644
00:37:15.335 --> 00:37:16.971
Might want to ask the
antiquities dealer

645
00:37:17.004 --> 00:37:18.472
we found impaled by one.

646
00:37:29.684 --> 00:37:32.587
"They watch you
at your hearth."

647
00:37:32.620 --> 00:37:33.721
Indeed.

648
00:37:36.389 --> 00:37:38.593
I'm merely the messenger.

649
00:37:38.626 --> 00:37:40.862
Well. I could've
saved you the trip.

650
00:37:40.895 --> 00:37:42.830
Please let the Court
know that I'm as unhappy

651
00:37:42.864 --> 00:37:45.633
with the hunt for Turner Hayes
and the others as they are.

652
00:37:45.666 --> 00:37:47.778
and you can assure them that
apprehending the fugitives

653
00:37:47.802 --> 00:37:49.537
is my top priority.

654
00:37:49.570 --> 00:37:51.271
But I might have
more time to devote

655
00:37:51.304 --> 00:37:52.840
to running our quarry to ground

656
00:37:52.874 --> 00:37:55.143
if I didn't have to
keep covering things up

657
00:37:55.176 --> 00:37:56.309
for their executioner.

658
00:37:56.343 --> 00:37:58.278
Wha... you didn't seem

659
00:37:58.311 --> 00:37:59.490
to have any complaints when he

660
00:37:59.514 --> 00:38:01.816
eliminated your rival years ago.

661
00:38:01.849 --> 00:38:02.917
Ha.

662
00:38:13.561 --> 00:38:17.031
Have you forgotten
your debt of gratitude?

663
00:38:19.100 --> 00:38:20.500
I haven't.

664
00:38:21.702 --> 00:38:23.104
Just keep me in office so I can

665
00:38:23.137 --> 00:38:24.572
continue to repay it.

666
00:38:50.798 --> 00:38:51.833
I'm sorry.

667
00:38:52.967 --> 00:38:55.069
I never meant for you to
get in so much trouble.

668
00:38:55.102 --> 00:38:56.237
It's OK.

669
00:38:56.270 --> 00:38:58.105
No. it's not.

670
00:38:58.139 --> 00:39:00.107
Helping me is just too risky.

671
00:39:00.141 --> 00:39:02.342
Says the guy who Catwomaned
his way into Wayne Tower

672
00:39:02.375 --> 00:39:04.377
and almost came out way shorter.

673
00:39:07.982 --> 00:39:10.885
At least now we know the
Court of Owls is real

674
00:39:10.918 --> 00:39:13.353
and we can use this
to clear our names.

675
00:39:13.386 --> 00:39:14.498
I just don't get how the Talon

676
00:39:14.522 --> 00:39:15.957
even knew you were there.

677
00:39:17.291 --> 00:39:19.392
I mean. you guys have to
heist your way in there

678
00:39:19.426 --> 00:39:23.064
dodging security guards.
cameras. motion sensors.

679
00:39:23.097 --> 00:39:24.665
and the Talon just

680
00:39:24.699 --> 00:39:27.500
cruises in and out of
there without a trace?

681
00:39:27.535 --> 00:39:29.704
Yeah. and that's not
the only mystery.

682
00:39:30.938 --> 00:39:31.973
Look at this.

683
00:39:33.307 --> 00:39:35.109
This is the last
one my dad wrote in.

684
00:39:35.142 --> 00:39:36.376
Anything interesting?

685
00:39:36.409 --> 00:39:39.747
Well. somebody
thought so. because...

686
00:39:39.780 --> 00:39:42.016
they ripped out his final entry.

687
00:39:42.049 --> 00:39:43.050
I don't get it.

688
00:39:44.318 --> 00:39:46.787
Why didn't they just
take the whole journal?

689
00:39:46.821 --> 00:39:49.857
I don't know. but whoever it was

690
00:39:49.891 --> 00:39:51.592
doesn't want us to
know what he wrote.

691
00:41:07.234 --> 00:41:08.936
Greg. move your head.
